com.newatlanta.appengine.vfs.provider
Class GaeFileObject

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.commons.vfs.provider.AbstractFileObject
      com.newatlanta.appengine.vfs.provider.GaeFileObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, org.apache.commons.vfs.FileObject
public class GaeFileObject
extends org.apache.commons.vfs.provider.AbstractFileObject
implements java.io.Serializable

Stores metadata for "files" and "folders" within GaeVFS and manages interactions with the Google App Engine datastore. This is an internal GaeVFS implementation class that is normally not referenced directly, but only indirectly via the Apache Commons VFS API. See GaeVFS as the entry point for application code that interacts with GaeVFS.

Author:
Vince Bonfanti

Returns the file type. The main use of this method is to determine if the file exists. As long as we always set the superclass type via injectType(), this method never gets invoked (which is a good thing, because it's expensive).

doListChildren

protected java.lang.String[] doListChildren()
                                     throws org.apache.commons.vfs.FileSystemException
Lists the children of this file. Is only called if doGetType() returns FileType.FOLDER. The return value of this method is cached, so the implementation can be expensive. GAE note: this method only lists the GAE children, and not the local children. But, with the current superclass implementation, this method is never invoked if doListChildrenResolved() is implemented (see below).

Specified by:
doListChildren in class org.apache.commons.vfs.provider.AbstractFileObject

Lists the children of this file. Is only called if doGetType() returns FileType.FOLDER. The return value of this method is cached, so the implementation can be expensive.
